    • Method Detail

      • consume

        public static void consume(long presentationTimeUs,
                           ParsableByteArray seiBuffer,
                           TrackOutput[] outputs)
        Consumes the unescaped content of an SEI NAL unit, writing the content of any CEA-608 messages as samples to all of the provided outputs.
        Parameters:
        presentationTimeUs - The presentation time in microseconds for any samples.
        seiBuffer - The unescaped SEI NAL unit data, excluding the NAL unit start code and type.
        outputs - The outputs to which any samples should be written.

      • readNon255TerminatedValue

        private static int readNon255TerminatedValue(ParsableByteArray buffer)
        Reads a value from the provided buffer consisting of zero or more 0xFF bytes followed by a terminating byte not equal to 0xFF. The returned value is ((0xFF * N) + T), where N is the number of 0xFF bytes and T is the value of the terminating byte.
        Parameters:
        buffer - The buffer from which to read the value.
        Returns:
        The read value, or -1 if the end of the buffer is reached before a value is read.

      • isSeiMessageCea608

        private static boolean isSeiMessageCea608(int payloadType,
                                          int payloadLength,
                                          ParsableByteArray payload)
        Inspects an sei message to determine whether it contains CEA-608.

        The position of payload is left unchanged.

        Parameters:
        payloadType - The payload type of the message.
        payloadLength - The length of the payload.
        payload - A ParsableByteArray containing the payload.
        Returns:
        Whether the sei message contains CEA-608.
